.TH DISCORD_TYPES 3 "2026-06-29" "libdiscord 0.2.0" "libdiscord Programmer's Manual"
.SH NAME
discord_types \\\\- Discord permission flags, intent bitfields, channel types, and message types
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
#include <discord_types.h>
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B discord_types.h
defines the fundamental enumerations used throughout libdiscord for Discord protocol constants. These are separated from
.B discord.h
to allow lightweight inclusion in type-aware code without pulling in the full API.
.SH PERMISSION FLAGS
.B discord_permission_t
defines the Discord permission bitfield flags (64-bit). These correspond to the permission overwrites in channel and role objects.

.TS
l l.
Flag	Bit
_
DISCORD_PERM_CREATE_INSTANT_INVITE	1 << 0
DISCORD_PERM_KICK_MEMBERS	1 << 1
DISCORD_PERM_BAN_MEMBERS	1 << 2
DISCORD_PERM_ADMINISTRATOR	1 << 3
DISCORD_PERM_MANAGE_CHANNELS	1 << 4
DISCORD_PERM_MANAGE_GUILD	1 << 5
DISCORD_PERM_ADD_REACTIONS	1 << 6
DISCORD_PERM_VIEW_AUDIT_LOG	1 << 7
DISCORD_PERM_SEND_MESSAGES	1 << 11
DISCORD_PERM_MANAGE_MESSAGES	1 << 13
DISCORD_PERM_EMBED_LINKS	1 << 14
DISCORD_PERM_ATTACH_FILES	1 << 15
DISCORD_PERM_READ_MESSAGE_HISTORY	1 << 16
DISCORD_PERM_MENTION_EVERYONE	1 << 18
DISCORD_PERM_USE_EXTERNAL_EMOJIS	1 << 18
DISCORD_PERM_CONNECT	1 << 20
DISCORD_PERM_SPEAK	1 << 21
DISCORD_PERM_MANAGE_ROLES	1 << 28
DISCORD_PERM_MANAGE_WEBHOOKS	1 << 29
.TE

.SH CHANNEL TYPES
.B discord_channel_type_t
identifies the type of a Discord channel.

.TS
l l.
Value	Type
_
0	GUILD_TEXT — standard text channel
1	DM — direct message
2	GUILD_VOICE — voice channel
3	GROUP_DM — group direct message
4	GUILD_CATEGORY — channel category
5	GUILD_ANNOUNCEMENT — announcement channel
6	GUILD_STORE — store channel
13	GUILD_STAGE_VOICE — stage channel
15	GUILD_FORUM — forum channel
.TE

.SH MESSAGE TYPES
.B discord_message_type_t
identifies the type of a Discord message.

.TS
l l.
Value	Type
_
0	DEFAULT — normal message
1	RECIPIENT_ADD — user added to group DM
2	RECIPIENT_REMOVE — user removed from group DM
3	CALL — voice/video call
4	CHANNEL_NAME_CHANGE — channel renamed
5	CHANNEL_ICON_CHANGE — channel icon changed
6	CHANNEL_PINNED_MESSAGE — message pinned
7	GUILD_MEMBER_JOIN — member joined guild
19	REPLY — message reply
20	APPLICATION_COMMAND — slash command
21	THREAD_STARTER_MESSAGE — thread starter
23	CONTEXT_MENU_COMMAND — context menu command
.TE

.SH GATEWAY INTENTS
.B discord_intent_t
is a bitfield for specifying which Gateway events the bot wants to receive in the identify payload.

.SS Non-privileged intents (always available)
.TS
l l.
Intent	Bit
_
DISCORD_INTENT_GUILDS	1 << 0
DISCORD_INTENT_GUILD_MODERATION	1 << 2
DISCORD_INTENT_GUILD_EXPRESSIONS	1 << 3
DISCORD_INTENT_GUILD_INTEGRATIONS	1 << 4
DISCORD_INTENT_GUILD_WEBHOOKS	1 << 5
DISCORD_INTENT_GUILD_INVITES	1 << 6
DISCORD_INTENT_GUILD_VOICE_STATES	1 << 7
DISCORD_INTENT_GUILD_MESSAGES	1 << 9
DISCORD_INTENT_GUILD_MESSAGE_REACTIONS	1 << 10
DISCORD_INTENT_GUILD_MESSAGE_TYPING	1 << 11
DISCORD_INTENT_DIRECT_MESSAGES	1 << 12
DISCORD_INTENT_DIRECT_MESSAGE_REACTIONS	1 << 13
DISCORD_INTENT_DIRECT_MESSAGE_TYPING	1 << 14
DISCORD_INTENT_GUILD_SCHEDULED_EVENTS	1 << 16
DISCORD_INTENT_AUTO_MODERATION_CONFIGURATION	1 << 20
DISCORD_INTENT_AUTO_MODERATION_EXECUTION	1 << 21
.TE

.SS Privileged intents (require Discord Developer Portal approval)
.TS
l l.
Intent	Bit
_
DISCORD_INTENT_GUILD_MEMBERS	1 << 1
DISCORD_INTENT_GUILD_PRESENCES	1 << 8
DISCORD_INTENT_MESSAGE_CONTENT	1 << 15
.TE

.B DISCORD_INTENTS_DEFAULT
is a convenience macro that combines all non-privileged intents. Used when
.B discord_config_t.intents
is set to 0.
.SH SEE ALSO
discord_create_with_config(3), discord_gateway_send_identify(3), discord.h(3)
.SH NOTES
All values are defined as C enums with explicit integer values to match the Discord API specification. Permission flags use 64-bit values (unsigned long long) to cover bits 0-53 per Discord's spec. Channel and message types use plain int.
